The paper deals with searching and ranking workflows based on keyword queries, which involves techniques from database systems (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of bag grammars to model workflows suggests a connection to natural language processing and deep learning (cs.DL). The development of a search and ranking solution involves software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
